title: Did a Woman Survive the Titanic, Hindenburg, Pearl Harbor, and 9/11?
subtitle: The life story of Anna Mae Dickinson, dubbed the "luckiest woman alive," is amazing — and fictional.
author: Dan Evon
vclaim: Anna Mae Dickinson survived a variety of infamous tragedies, including the sinking of the Titanic, the Hindenburg explosion, and the 9/11 terrorist attacks.
